{"TopicId":176716,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Terminate all debris","CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T09:27:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T09:27:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know we can set max debris, but can we add a button to terminate all debris to reduce the time required to clear a crime scene?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T10:36:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have SO much debris. I\u0027d like it if this was possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T11:02:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems like a good quality of life addition.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T12:51:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is actually a mod to do this \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3479272395\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/176025-14x-mr-clean-and-his-magic-eraser-remove-debris-the-easy-way-61918/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3401891\u0026amp;embedComment=3401891\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3401891\u0022 style=\u0022height:313px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t get me wrong...it would be nice to have such a feature in stock but you might want a solution right now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-14T13:26:11Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2018 01:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by 4x4cheesecake\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-14T13:52:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust go into your settings and lower the max debris slider to zero.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLoad your game up, save. Go back to menu and raise max debris to whatever you had it at.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo more debris.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-14T13:52:55Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2018 01:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-15T17:19:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223415483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531576343\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/14/2018 at 9:52 AM, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust go into your settings and lower the max debris slider to zero.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLoad your game up, save. Go back to menu and raise max debris to whatever you had it at.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo more debris.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you can install Mr. Clean as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187982-4x4cheesecake/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187982\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187982-4x4cheesecake/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@4x4cheesecake\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0mentioned above and have it cleared in 1 click of a button instead of this save/change settings/ save again/change settings back/save again and then reload\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to me it would take literally seconds using Mr. Clean and minutes if not dozens of minutes doing it your way\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223415456\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531572671\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187982\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00224x4cheesecake\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/14/2018 at 8:51 AM, 4x4cheesecake said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is actually a mod to do this \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2014178065\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/176025-14x-mr-clean-and-his-magic-eraser-remove-debris-the-easy-way-61918/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3401891\u0026amp;embedComment=3401891\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3401891\u0022 style=\u0022height:329px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t get me wrong...it would be nice to have such a feature in stock but you might want a solution right now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-15T17:20:21Z\u0022 title=\u002207/15/2018 05:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by DoctorDavinci\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-15T17:46:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223416019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531675188\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you can install Mr. Clean as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187982-4x4cheesecake/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187982\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187982-4x4cheesecake/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@4x4cheesecake\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0mentioned above and have it cleared in 1 click of a button instead of this save/change settings/ save again/change settings back/save again and then reload\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to me it would take literally seconds using Mr. Clean and minutes if not dozens of minutes doing it your way\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, just offering an alternative for those who may be opposed to modding, or unable to use mods. (Console players.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-15T19:42:18Z\u0022 title=\u002207/15/2018 07:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ariscol","CreatedById":170688,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-25T06:22:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh man, I love this idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I may, however, I\u0027d go a little further than just an option to delete all debris. I think it\u0027d be super-nice, if, in the tracking station, you could filter not only by craft type, but also by \u003Cu\u003Ename\u003C/u\u003E, and then we would just need a\u00A0 \u0022DELETE ALL\u0022 button that would delete all craft that were currently in your list (based on your selected craft type(s) and partial name).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat way I could not only delete all debris, but I could also, say, delete all debris from a particular craft (e.h. debris with \u0022Minmus Lander\u0022 in the name), or all relay satellites with the name \u0022Duna 1st expedition\u0022, etc.. That\u0027d be so flexible, it\u0027d be a huge help for those of us who are neurotic about keeping things clean.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MR L A","CreatedById":150940,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-28T12:05:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d sooner have the ability to select multiple craft at once in the tracking station... I only delete debris on suborbital trajectories \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-29T14:03:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223421741\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221532499751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170688\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ariscol\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/25/2018 at 2:22 AM, ariscol said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh man, I love this idea!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I may, however, I\u0027d go a little further than just an option to delete all debris. I think it\u0027d be super-nice, if, in the tracking station, you could filter not only by craft type, but also by \u003Cu\u003Ename\u003C/u\u003E, and then we would just need a\u00A0 \u0022DELETE ALL\u0022 button that would delete all craft that were currently in your list (based on your selected craft type(s) and partial name).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat way I could not only delete all debris, but I could also, say, delete all debris from a particular craft (e.h. debris with \u0022Minmus Lander\u0022 in the name), or all relay satellites with the name \u0022Duna 1st expedition\u0022, etc.. That\u0027d be so flexible, it\u0027d be a huge help for those of us who are neurotic about keeping things clean.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is a good idea ... I may just add the functionality you describe to Mr Clean\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-30T05:30:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here I am, being a responsible Kerbal and making sure all my debris de-orbits on it\u0027s own.... like a sucker!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-30T07:14:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso KerboKatz DestroyAll can do this nicely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4117880244\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/104505-14x-kerbokatz-smallutilities-28042018/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-23T00:38:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223424428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176716\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221532928617\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114432\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mahnarch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/30/2018 at 1:30 AM, Mahnarch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here I am, being a responsible Kerbal and making sure all my debris de-orbits on it\u0027s own.... like a sucker!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem is when you accidentally crash a base and can not revert the flight \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}